{"TopicId":219339,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Add raster lines to capture mode","CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T19:14:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T19:14:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally doesn\u0027t need further explanation:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrent:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1039965578754007060/1149058760703226018/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuggested:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u002280.75\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/625661934762721303/1149059569235021844/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T20:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore than that, what we really need is a proper photo mode interface (and feature), like quite a few games:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.30\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 style=\u0022width:1000px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 alt=\u0022Pj5V4vH.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Pj5V4vH.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.30\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 style=\u0022width:1000px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022xaTjndX.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/xaTjndX.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe time of the day feature might be a bit complex in ksp but I would take some filters/effects or depth of field anytime.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-07T09:53:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t get it, what are these lines for?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-08T10:05:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320182\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694080380\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/7/2023 at 11:53 AM, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t get it, what are these lines for?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/225622-periple/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/225622-periple/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Periple\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0It allows you to make screenshots that are good from a technical perspective. If you you only care about screenshots then it\u0027s not important, but if you want symmetry, correct alignments, perfectly centred objects, etc., this becomes a necessity.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI especially like what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022228085\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spicat\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0mentioned. The guidelines are helpful, but a complete photo mode would be amazing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-08T10:08:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320468\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694167533\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222638\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Abelinoss\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Abelinoss said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt allows you to make screenshots that are good from a technical perspective. If you you only care about screenshots then it\u0027s not important, but if you want symmetry, correct alignments, perfectly centred objects, etc., this becomes a necessity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still don\u0027t understand, how do the lines make it possible to get screenshots that are good from a technical perspective? What even is correct alignment? Is this like the so-called \u0022rule of thirds\u0022 in photography?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-09T10:05:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694167720\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still don\u0027t understand, how do the lines make it possible to get screenshots that are good from a technical perspective? What even is correct alignment? Is this like the so-called \u0022rule of thirds\u0022 in photography?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtreme example:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?width=972\u0026amp;height=676\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.55\u0022 height=\u0022676\u0022 width=\u0022972\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/625661934762721303/1150008371303424020/image.png?width=972\u0026amp;height=676\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.68\u0022 height=\u0022672\u0022 width=\u00221039\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/625661934762721303/1150008400848101397/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nObviously, the second photo has a better alignment, but it\u0027s still not perfect. Those camera lines can help in such a case. But there are many more uses that guidelines can help to make photos of higher quality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Datau03","CreatedById":223270,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-17T11:01:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320054\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694031688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/6/2023 at 10:21 PM, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore than that, what we really need is a proper photo mode interface (and feature), like quite a few games:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Pj5V4vH.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Pj5V4vH.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.30\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 style=\u0022width:1000px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Pj5V4vH.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/xaTjndX.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022xaTjndX.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.30\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 style=\u0022width:1000px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/xaTjndX.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe time of the day feature might be a bit complex in ksp but I would take some filters/effects or depth of field anytime.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazing would be a way to replay craft flights and film cinematics out of them\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-17T16:31:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022228085\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spicat\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/xBD7IOI8vAo?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Cinematic Camera \u0026amp; Photo Mode I Feature Highlights Ep 13 I Cities: Skylines II\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven better like Cities Skylines 2 will do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth a complete photomode, and a cinematic mode with an intuitive keypoints on a timeline for videos\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}